The paper focuses on face authentication systems and proposes a new liveness detection protocol based on analyzing light reflections. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and computer security (cs.CR) categories. The paper also mentions the use of deep learning technologies, which is a common topic in the multimedia (cs.MM) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed protocol in real-world scenarios, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
